cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF, cs.MA 

The paper deals with the analysis and design of a feedback controller for regulating queueing delay in a next generation edge transport architecture for 802.11ac WLANs. This involves modelling, control analysis and design, and performance evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with control theory and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of a proportional fair optimization problem for control design suggests that it could also belong to cs.PF (Performance Analysis of Systems and Networks). Finally, the use of simulations and experimental measurements suggests that it could also belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
